DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260316
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260317
SUMMARY:Revolution & Reflection: Campus Experiences in Art\, History\, an
 d Ideas
DESCRIPTION:Look for your guide\, President George Washington\, as you dr
 op in to visit these three revolutionary destinations:The Lilly Library p
 resents The Declaration of Independence: The Motives\, The Moment (https:
 //libraries.indiana.edu/lilly-library/declaration-independence).The Sidne
 y and Lois Eskenazi Museum of Art showcases George Washington's portrait 
 by Gilbert Stuart.  IU Auditorium is the caretaker of Thomas Hart Benton'
 s iconic murals (https://www.iuauditorium.com/about-us/benton-murals-orga
 n-and-dailey-art-collection)\, titled The Social History of Indiana.Spend
  an afternoon with us. Or a whole day. This self-guided offering is desig
 ned to allow you to create your own educational experience. Visit all loc
 ations in one trip or come back to campus multiple times. Each Fine Arts 
 Plaza destination has different operating hours\; please consult them car
 efully when planning your trip. All locations are open Tuesdayâ€“Friday b
 etween 10 a.m. and 5 p.m.  Check our online event calendar at go.iu.edu/a
 merica-250 (https://go.iu.edu/america-250) for special events and additio
 nal campus celebrations of America's 250th.  To schedule a tour for group
 s of students in grades 2-12\, see Field Trip Tours: Revolution &amp\; Re
 flection (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/visit/museum-tours/tour-types.htm
 l).&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Look for your guide\, President George 
 Washington\, as you drop in to visit these three revolutionary destinatio
 ns:</p><ul><li><strong>The Lilly Library</strong> presents <em><a href="h
 ttps://libraries.indiana.edu/lilly-library/declaration-independence">The 
 Declaration of Independence: The Motives\, The Moment</a>.</em></li><li><
 strong>The Sidney and Lois Eskenazi Museum of Art</strong> showcases Geor
 ge Washington's portrait by Gilbert Stuart.  </li><li><strong>IU Auditori
 um</strong> is the caretaker of <a href="https://www.iuauditorium.com/abo
 ut-us/benton-murals-organ-and-dailey-art-collection" target="_blank" rel=
 "noopener">Thomas Hart Benton's iconic murals</a>\, titled <em>The Social
  History of Indiana.</em></li></ul><p><strong>Spend an afternoon with us.
  Or a whole day.</strong> This self-guided offering is designed to allow 
 you to create your own educational experience. Visit all locations in one
  trip or come back to campus multiple times. Each Fine Arts Plaza destina
 tion has different operating hours\; please consult them carefully when p
 lanning your trip. <strong>All locations are open Tuesdayâ€“Friday betwee
 n 10 a.m. and 5 p.m.</strong></p><p>  Check our online event calendar at 
 <a href="https://go.iu.edu/america-250">go.iu.edu/america-250</a> for spe
 cial events and additional campus celebrations of America's 250th.</p><p>
   To schedule a tour for groups of <strong>students in grades 2-12</stron
 g>\, see <a href="https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/visit/museum-tours/tour-t
 ypes.html">Field Trip Tours: Revolution &amp\; Reflection</a>.&#160\;</p>
